description: Lists your rescore execution plans. A rescore execution plan is an Amazon Kendra Intelligent Ranking resource used for provisioning the Rescore API.

nested_items.name: SummaryItems
nested_items.description: An array of summary information for one or more rescore execution plans.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the rescore execution plan.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The identifier of the rescore execution plan.

nested_items.name: CreatedAt
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp when the rescore execution plan was created.

nested_items.name: UpdatedAt
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp when the rescore execution plan was last updated.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The current status of the rescore execution plan. When the value is ACTIVE, the rescore execution plan is ready for use.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If the response is truncated, Amazon Kendra Intelligent Ranking returns a pagination token in the response.
